  1. reading excel-file and marking missing values as NA. Relevant columns are âEast Coordâ,âNorth Coordâ, âStart Dateâ, and âactivityâ. The coordinates UTM coordinates (UTM zone 33N, EPSG code 25833).
otter_vestland <- read_excel("ExcelExport_7972978_Page_1a.xlsx",
                                  skip = 2,
                                  na = c("", "NA")) |>
                                    janitor::clean_names()  |>
  select(east_coord, north_coord, start_date, municipality, activity)
  1. extracting relevant columns and column-data/relevant activities: âRoadkillâ, âDrowned in fishing netâ, and âFound deadâ, all after 2019. Also extracting relevant coordinates
otter_vestland <- otter_vestland |>
  filter(start_date >= '2019-01-01') 

otter_vestland <-  subset(otter_vestland,
         activity %in% c("Roadkill", "Drowned in fishing net", "Found dead")
)
otter_vestland_sf <- st_as_sf(otter_vestland, coords = c("east_coord", "north_coord"), crs = 25833)
  1. making the map. FIGURE 1.1
norway <- ne_countries(scale = 10, returnclass = "sf", country = "Norway") #importing map of norway from rnaturalearth with high res. 


#making these variables so that title name will be dynamic, that is if we want to look at different dates, the plot title will automatically change to selected period. 
min_date <- min(otter_vestland_sf$start_date, na.rm = TRUE)
max_date <- max(otter_vestland_sf$start_date, na.rm = TRUE)


#making initial plot in ggplot
vestland_map <-
  ggplot() +
    geom_sf(data = norway) +
    annotation_map_tile("cartolight") +
    geom_sf(data = otter_vestland_sf, aes(color = activity), size = 1.5) +
    coord_sf(xlim = c(4, 9.2), ylim = c(59, 62.1)) +
    geom_line() +
    labs(title = paste("Cause of otter death, Vestland, ", min_date, "to", max_date))

4.1) Adding more layers of information to the map. FIGURE 1.2. This is the figure I wish to be evaluated on for this assignment.

vestland_map_otter_plot <-
  ggplot() +
    geom_sf(data = norway) +
    annotation_map_tile("cartolight") +
    geom_sf(data = otter_vestland_sf, aes(color = municipality,
                                          shape = activity,
                                          alpha = 0.7), size = 1.5) +
    coord_sf(xlim = c(4, 8), ylim = c(59, 62)) 
  
final_map <- vestland_map_otter_plot + 
  guides(alpha = FALSE) +
  theme(legend.position = "left", legend.box = "vertical") +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = paste("Otter Death, Vestland, ", min_date, "to", max_date))
Warning: The `<scale>` argument of `guides()` cannot be `FALSE`. Use "none" instead as

  1. Additional figure below: Although this is no longer part of the assignment, I think it conveys interesting information information: The point of which sightings called âfound deadâ drop off, âdrowned in fishing netâ picks up. Perhaps this is something one should take note of before eventually using the data.
otter_plot <- ggplot(
  data = otter_vestland_sf, aes(x = start_date, y = activity, color = municipality, alpha = 0.7)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(x = "", y = "") +
  theme_minimal()

otter_plot <- otter_plot + guides(alpha = FALSE) + theme_update()

otter_plot

  1. combining plots using patchwork, but mostly for own practice.
combo_plot <- 
  (final_map + guides(color = FALSE) + 
   theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, vjust = 10)))  + 
   otter_plot + theme(legend.position = c(-1.2, -0.35),
                      legend.direction = ("horizontal")) #aligning title
